The skim function at Pair.sol lines 230-234 reads:

function skim(address to) external lock {
    (address _token0, address _token1) = (token0, token1);
    _safeTransfer(_token0, to, IERC20(_token0).balanceOf(address(this)) - (reserve0));
    _safeTransfer(_token1, to, IERC20(_token1).balanceOf(address(this)) - (reserve1));
}

This is identical in behavior to the original Uniswap V2 Pair contract's skim function. The lock modifier provides reentrancy protection. The function correctly calculates excess as balance minus reserve for both tokens. There is no code defect here - it is an intentional design choice inherited from the Uniswap V2 protocol specification.
